<item>
            <title>[JXPATH-109] Namespaced attribute not selected with wildcard</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXPATH-109</link>
                <project id="12310480" key="JXPATH">Commons JXPath</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With expression:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;xml/@*&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On xml:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;xml xmlns:x=&apos;foo&apos; x:pop=&apos;a&apos;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;selectSingleNode returns null, @x:* works fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Possible Fix:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In DOMAttributeIterator, line 84&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (equalStrings(testPrefix, nodePrefix)) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                return true;
            }&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
should probably be changed to&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
if (testPrefix==null || equalStrings(testPrefix, nodePrefix)) {                return true;            }</description>
